        <h1>Rescue and Emergency Planning Department</h1>
        
        <div class="pageDescription"><p align="left">The Rescue and Emergency Planning Department is the superior authority to the Directorate for Civil Defence and Emergency Planning. The department is responsible for coordinating the Norwegian Rescue Service and has the administrative responsibility for the main rescue coordination centre. The department also administers Civilian National Service in Norway.</p>
<p align="left"><i>The department is divided into three units.</i></p>
<p align="left"><b>Rescue Service Unit</b> coordinates the administration of the Rescue Service in Norway, including follow-up of bilateral and multilateral agreements entered into by the Ministry of Justice and the main rescue coordination centres. The unit is also responsible for administration of the two main rescue coordination centres.</p>
<p align="left"><b>Emergency Planning Unit</b> has the responsibility for the Ministry’s internal security and emergency planning, including responsibility for data security. The unit has a comprehensive, multisectoral responsibility for coordination of emergency planning, where each ministry has independent sectoral responsibility. This means that all proposals for new or major amendments to current laws and regulations in the area of emergency planning shall be submitted to the Ministry for comment. The unit coordinates budget proposals associated with the fiscal budget and long-term plans for civil emergency preparedness.</p>
<p align="left">The unit is also responsible for management of the Directorate for Civil Defence and Emergency Planning, including the Civil Defence. Through cooperation with the County Governors, the Directorate shall establish conditions to enable the municipalities to prevent and deal with crisis situations both in peacetime and wartime.</p>
<p align="left"><b>Civilian National Service Unit.</b> The Ministry of Justice is responsible for organizing the Civilian National Service in Norway, including overall responsibility for processing applications for exemption, and for assigning persons objecting to military service to relevant duties and preparing them to be able to make a contribution in emergency situations. The Civilian National Service Unit has responsibility for the Civilian National Service administrations and for preliminary training of civilian national servicemen.</p><a name="hov0.0.1"></a><a name="hov.ing.0.1"></a>
<h3 align="left">Subordinate agencies:</h3>
<ul type="disc">
<li>Directorate for Civil Defence and Emergency Planning </li>
<li>Rescue Coordination Centre Northern Norway </li>
<li>Rescue Coordination Centre Southern Norway </li>
<li>Civilian National Service Administration Dillingøy </li>
<li>Civilian National Service Administration Hustad </li></ul></div>        
